00:37:58,640 --> 00:38:02,620
To answer that question, we need to do something more.

537
00:38:02,620 --> 00:38:07,520
And that's what requires that we reconsider what we think the living state is and what

538
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:12,200
the right kind of formal model for it is.

539
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:16,400
I want to argue that the way to understand, the way that makes sense of the fact that

540
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:21,840
life emerged on a lifeless earth and that it has persisted for almost four billion years

541
00:38:21,840 --> 00:38:26,280
since is the concept of breakdown or failure.

542
00:38:26,280 --> 00:38:31,360
So remember that we're trying to understand a pattern of motion.

543
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:35,040
Breakdown creates patterns of motion at the same time as it destroys certain patterns

544
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:36,960
of structure.

545
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:40,400
So things don't only fall apart.

546
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:46,720
Sometimes the events become ordered even as the structures are broken.

547
00:38:46,720 --> 00:38:52,640
And so we have the concept that the origin of life could be a kind of collapse.

548
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:58,080
And once you have a collapse, the idea that when pushed hard enough, anything will give,

549
00:38:58,080 --> 00:39:01,480
that brings with it the notion of necessity.

550
00:39:01,480 --> 00:39:07,400
Because in the world of breakdowns, the things that persist are only the things that were

551
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:13,200
the favored state or the necessary state to begin with.

552
00:39:13,200 --> 00:39:14,880
Now this is not an exotic idea.

553
00:39:14,880 --> 00:39:20,200
It turns out that it's around us all the time.

554
00:39:20,200 --> 00:39:26,280
The main thing you need in order to understand it is the idea of an energy flow channel.

555
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:29,520
There are lots of energy flow channels in the natural world.

556
00:39:29,520 --> 00:39:30,520
Lightning is one.

557
00:39:30,520 --> 00:39:34,720
We create a plasma that's very, very, very different from the surrounding dry air, but

558
00:39:34,720 --> 00:39:36,760
it allows electricity to flow.

559
00:39:36,760 --> 00:39:41,520
We create all this organization of wall storms in a cyclone because that transports heat

560
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:44,320
from the warm oceans to the upper atmosphere.

561
00:39:44,320 --> 00:39:49,040
And this is not the disordered pattern of just thunderstorms or uniformly mixed air.

562
00:39:49,040 --> 00:39:56,160
So these things are well understood in the physical sciences already.

563
00:39:56,160 --> 00:40:00,640
The thing that's important to create a channel and the reason not all things form channels

564
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:03,040
is that there needs to be feedback.

565
00:40:03,040 --> 00:40:06,160
Because in all of these systems, the initial stress is diffuse.

566
00:40:06,160 --> 00:40:09,640
The clouds have a charge spread out over a great distance.

567
00:40:09,640 --> 00:40:12,280
Or the oceans are warm over an enormous volume.

568
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:18,200
But the ice storms concentrate only in one area because that moves things more.

569
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:21,920
So I'll illustrate for you dynamically with the simplest of all channels, which is just

570
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:25,120
the propagation of a fracture.

571
00:40:25,120 --> 00:40:29,040
If you could see a fracture propagating at the atomic scale, you would see that it's

572
00:40:29,040 --> 00:40:34,340
a self-similar repeating sequence of events as bond after bond breaks.

573
00:40:34,340 --> 00:40:40,360
The reason this is striking is that in the original crystal, there's plenty of energy

574
00:40:40,360 --> 00:40:43,600
in the crystal as a whole to break the bonds.

575
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:45,480
But the energy is too diffuse.

576
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:49,360
And so by itself, it can't concentrate to rupture a bond.

577
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:53,880
The thing that causes the fracture to propagate in an orderly way instead of happening at

578
00:40:53,880 --> 00:40:59,840
random everywhere is that the stress field in the surround, as it deforms, pulls the

579
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:05,720
stress from the bulk back down to atomic diameters and concentrates it.

580
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:09,320
This is what hydrothermal vents are doing for the Earth battery, because the battery

581
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:12,640
is accumulating over the entire atmosphere and interior.

582
00:41:12,640 --> 00:41:17,120
But it's being focused at the regions where rock contacts water and the regions where

583
00:41:17,120 --> 00:41:20,600
the altered water remixes with seawater.

584
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:25,200
Now I want to show you that this is actually what the citric acid cycle does within chemistry.

585
00:41:25,200 --> 00:41:29,600
It performs a second kind of concentration.

586
00:41:29,600 --> 00:41:35,160
So as the molecule goes around, it pulls in carbon, and then here it splits.

587
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:37,320
And both parts go back into the cycle.

588
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:39,800
So where you had one, you now have two.

589
00:41:39,800 --> 00:41:42,520
That's the mathematics of compound interest.

590
00:41:42,520 --> 00:41:47,320
And so you can exponentially grow and you concentrate material within the cycle.

591
00:41:47,320 --> 00:41:52,320
Also like compound interest on an endowment, you can pull molecules off of this to make

592
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:58,640
your major classes of biological matter, but the material in the cycle is still available

593
00:41:58,640 --> 00:42:03,600
to serve as a kind of flypaper that continues to pull carbon in over and over again.

594
00:42:03,600 --> 00:42:06,440
So this is the second concentration.

595
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:12,160
Now the thing, this leads to an important way of thinking about the nature of life.

596
00:42:12,160 --> 00:42:16,320
You could imagine that the optimization of this cycle was something carried out by evolution

597
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:21,360
later, but I think there's actually a better way to view it.

598
00:42:21,360 --> 00:42:23,400
This cycle is self-amplifying.

599
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:25,880
It works from the environmental sources of carbon.

600
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:31,280
It works from the Earth's sources of electrons and everything in the biosphere is made from

601
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:33,040
it.

602
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:37,800
The biosphere is what you can make if these are the compounds you have.

603
00:42:37,800 --> 00:42:45,600
And so this is why it becomes the core that organizes the whole rest of metabolism.

604
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:48,400
So does this give us a complete theory of origins?

605
00:42:48,400 --> 00:42:49,400
Not nearly.

606
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:51,600
There's a lot of work to be done.

607
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:58,080
There are many problems to be solved and maybe many generations, maybe centuries of work

608
00:42:58,080 --> 00:43:02,360
before we have a satisfactory theory the way we have a theory of matter, but it fundamentally

609
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:05,840
changes the way we ask questions.

610
00:43:05,840 --> 00:43:09,520
When Darwin was trying to understand the origin of the world, even though he was a consummate

